        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:12AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 412 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Schroeder, or 8 miles northeast of Goliad, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fannin, Mission Valley, Schroeder, Coleto Creek Park, Ander, and
Nursery.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 183 near mile marker 638.
US Highway 59 between mile markers 654 and 660.
US Highway 87 between mile markers 800 and 802.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
